Nigerian human rights activist and convener of the Concerned Nigerians group, Deji Adeyanju, has bemoaned the values and standards of the current generation in the country. The former Head of New Media for the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) disclosed this in a post via his Instagram page, expressing that the people of this present generation only care about sex, vibes and free money. Adeyanju wrote, “This generation is one of the most hopeless ever. All they care about is sex , vibes and free money. Once you find someone that offers more with strong values, try your best to keep them. Buratai Boasts Of Modernised Nigerian Army Tricycle Riders Seek Separation From NURTW, Independent Union “Sensible people in this generation may be less than 10k. Both the men and women are the same.”